g.text: You: "I want to ask again about the people you don't like."
Jump to: [The Deserter: "His lip curls into a sneer at the m..."]
Cuno: "Fuck yeah, this is happening," he comments breathlessly, in awe of the potential violence implied.
Half Light: The danger levels here are hard to read. One moment he's a fire, the next -- a fire gone out.
Encyclopedia: It's almost as if they were never there. Only the rifle remains, cradled by the old man.
The Deserter: "In Graad they sang 'Brave Children, Favourites of History' and in Hsin-Yao it was..." He struggles to remember, then gives up. "...some Samaran shit, I guess."
Encyclopedia: In Hsin-Yao they sang "Boy with a Scythe / Golden Sun."
You: "It's as he said: it's a Triangong. Made in Hsin-Yao."
"It's as you said. This is a Triangong."
The Deserter: "It's not how a human being should live, but I had to..." He grimaces, clearly in pain. "...I couldn't just forget. I couldn't just forget what I saw."
Conceptualization: So that's why he's 'the deserter.'
Suggestion: What *has* he done? Perhaps a confession will lighten the load...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes -- what? To get things going again..." The lieutenant steps closer. "Fan the flame?"
The Deserter: "There is no flame to fan." He stares right through at him, blinking his dark eyes. "There is nothing left -- of the world, of our dreams."

The Deserter: "The combined might of international capital, all at once -- all the greed and terror in the world -- tore into Revachol. It lifted streets from the ground and turned houses into ghosts. We were in the flak tower..." He gestures toward it.

The Deserter: "...huddled on the floor. The artillery was eighty kilometres away in Ozonne but I *knew*, I knew the Commune would fall. We would all be turned into ash. So I said I was going to the map room..." He looks east.
The Deserter: The old man does not say more. Those black eyes of his keep piercing you, as he looks to some great distance and shakes his head slowly -- retreating from it.
Conceptualization: These eyes are charred black by the images that have entered them.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Now is not the time, detective..." The lieutenant says, gently.
"Now is not the time, Lieutenant-Yefreitor..." The lieutenant says, gently.

The Deserter: "I had to. I *had* to fight it. I could not stop anymore..." The old man falls silent. His black eyes keep piercing your skin as he looks to some great distance behind you, shaking his head slowly -- retreating from it.
You: "That's right. I'm with the good guys."
"That's right. We're with the good guys."

The Deserter: "Murderers..." He stares at the embers, then into your eyes. "You're the RCM -- you represent the Moralist International, the enemies of humanity, who took this city. I represent their adversary, le Parti communiste d'Insulinde."

The Deserter: "Take me to them as a prisoner of war. I have relinquished my weapon, I can no longer serve. No superiors can relieve me of my duty, you bulldozed them all to a mass grave for trying to free humanity..." His hand shakes and he breaks into a coughing fit.
The Deserter: "If the Party had surrendered -- then it would not be the Party."
He just wipes the blood from his chin.
The Deserter: "The what now?" He cups his ear. "I can't hear you."
You: "Did you recently tell two kids to put out their fire? Two twins."
You: "We have *drouamine*. And other opioid based painkillers. You must be in pain."
The Deserter: "I *have* been running out of that stuff..." A light goes on in his eyes. He smacks his dry lips.
The Deserter: He looks at you, his face parched from the sun and the wind -- there's a wince of pain in there somewhere.
Empathy: Are they not heartbroken? How could they have moved on?
You: "Ever smoke them on the mainland?" (Point to Land's End.)
The Deserter: "And others too. Some cordons of Revachol were still fighting. There were cells, I tried to contact them..." He shakes his head. "Soon they all went silent. The frequencies, dead."
You: "How did you get between here and the mainland?"

The Deserter: "At night. I used a dinghy..." He nods toward the deflated tyre in the reeds. "I only went after dark then. When I got to the city I stayed underground. Patrols. You lot. The commons too, they'd started snitching..."
The Deserter: "Sleeping..." He coughs. "Some nights. Ammo-scrounging on others. Those Magraves were shit even before they corroded -- some had bullets in the chamber, however."
Visual Calculus: You *feel* the dots connecting. Little dots on the map he's walked across.
Savoir Faire: Are you sure? Forget about it then...
The Deserter: The old man looks across the water: at the city, the ruins, the motorways rising above it...
The old man looks inland: at the city, the ruins, the motorways rising above it. The new *batiments* twinkling in the night sky.
The old man looks inland: at the city, the ruins, the motorways rising above it. The new *batiments* twinkling in the evening sky.
The Deserter: The old man stares at the reeds. His face shows no emotion -- only a faint tremor passes over his features, like a leaf in the wind.
Jump to: [Cuno: ""The fuck?!" Cuno's looking at you..."]
Cuno: "The fuck?!" Cuno's looking at you like you just shat yourself.
You: "No, I really am a communist. I have communist thoughts in my head."
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""What?!" The old man's eyes fill wi..."]
Savoir Faire: The *position*? Sounds like a hiding place...
The Deserter: "Fire-guy..." He shakes his head. "Regressive bourgeoisie henchman. Can't even talk like a grown up."
You: "Sorry for disturbing you. Good bye."
You: i wanna see phasmid with kim
You: "You don't like this uniform?" (Gesture toward your coat.)
You: "Did you close the blast door?"
You: "Sir, I need you to put down that gun so we can talk further. I'm with the police." (Proceed.)
"Sir, I need you to put down that gun so we can talk further. We're with the police." (Proceed.)
You: i wanna see phasmid with cuno
You: "I'm with the police. You can keep the gun, but keep it down. Not *one* move." (Proceed.)
You: "Your weapon has stayed true to you. Mine has stayed true to me too." (Put your hand on your belt.)
"Your weapon has stayed true to you. Mine has stayed true to me too." (Show him the gun in your hand.)
Authority: It's a good line, but your voice slips on *commander*, producing a little squeak. Sounds like you're afraid.
It's a good line but your voice slips on *commander*, producing a miserly little squeak. Sounds like you're afraid.
The Deserter: "A big time operator of the pederast army. How about I keep it, huh? Hand it over to a real killer. A *briscade*."
Encyclopedia: It's war time slang for an experienced soldier of high rank. From the days of the Revolution in Revachol.
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""It's out of bullets." The old man..."]
The Deserter: "It's out of bullets." The old man lays the rifle down, carelessly -- then stares at it, just lying there.
The Deserter: "The future teaches you to be alone."
The Deserter: "It is the anthem of the World Revolution." His eyes remain fixed on the sky. "One of three."
The Deserter: "It's the *drugs* you're all on. Druggies, winos, and whores..." He closes his eyes in disgust.
Drama: There was something there -- when he said *talked to her*? He was curious...
Kim Kitsuragi: "It doesn't matter if it was made in Shantih-Shantih. All it has to do is use jacketed ammunition. And it does."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Worn. Personalized even. Looks like this weapon has seen a lot of use. Hasn't it, sir?"
The Deserter: "Yes. Recruited from Jamrock in '07, trained in the Ecole de Contrle Arien; consigned to emergency defence duties in '08."

The Deserter: "I left my unit on the eve of the Landing. When I returned here on May 14th the Commune had fallen. Still armed -- and *ideologically trained* -- I wrote a criticism of myself. And resumed partisan duties."
The Deserter: "The fascists were right about rock-and-roll. It *is* degenerate... Hip-gyrating mental illness music."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Told you we shouldn't play Sad FM."
The Deserter: "Women *are* more susceptible to bourgeois morals." He blinks his black eyes. "The material base for an uprising has eroded, the working class has betrayed mankind and themselves..."
The Deserter: "The historic opportunity for a revolution has passed. It will not come back anymore. However hard I try, whatever I do."
You: This is not the time to push.
The Deserter: The old man suddenly looks around, confused. "What *can* I do? What is there..."
The Deserter: "For Reaction to take hold."
You: "Yes. We all have a tiny bourgeois person in us, trying to run away."
You: "It wasn't Reaction -- you were just afraid."
You: "I understand. Communists are natural cowards. Quantity over quality."

The Deserter: "The mask of humanity fall from capital. It has to take it off to kill everyone -- everything you love; all the hope and tenderness in the world. It has to take it off, just for one second. To do the deed."

The Deserter: "And then you see it. As it strangles and beats your friends to death... the sweetest, most courageous people in the world." He's silent for a second. "You see the fear and power in its eyes. Then you *know*."
You: "You mean the Landing? Retaking of Revachol?"
The Deserter: "Coalition military called it Operation *Death Blow*." He winces. "I later found out, on the radio. They called it..."
The Deserter: "Sure you are, you're RCM. Answer me -- who calls an operation against 50 million people *Death Blow*?"
You: "Murderers. I know what you mean."
You: "Someone who's come to end this madness."
You: "But you said you were trained and assigned to the Defence Corps."
The Deserter: "Trained," he nods, "in *historical materialism*, then assigned as a *political commissar*. By the Party. These things used to mean something."
You: (Point to yourself.) "I'm also a communist."
You: "By the way, I'm a fascist."
You: "I'm a nationalist by the way."
You: "I'm a revolutionary too. Today the real revolutionizing is done by entrepreneurs."
You: "I'm not really into politics myself."
The Deserter: "I've been throwing up blood since winter. Red, like beet root -- been passing it in stool too..."
Visual Calculus: He does seem frail, gaunt for his age, more like 75 than 65. Trouble putting on weight could mean cancer.
The Deserter: He coughs, then looks to his feet, suddenly despondent.
The Deserter: "It's disgusting..." He looks down at his shoes; his face parched from the sun and the wind -- there's a wince of pain in there somewhere.
You: "So in the city you move... underground?"

The Deserter: "From bunker to bunker..." He nods. "Not anymore, no one cares now, I don't even have to hide. They think I'm another antisocial vagrant. I could walk straight into that town if I wanted. I just..." He falls silent, his gaze fixed on the shacks huddled together across the water.
You: "Why don't you just walk there?"
The Deserter: "I don't want to. They're all traitors -- pigs, rabbits, and dogs. Men without ideals are only animals."
You: "There's a small bunker under the Feld building. Have you stayed there?"
The Deserter: "The propaganda bunker?" He coughs. "I used to, but not anymore."
Savoir Faire: Wait! How did he get down there?

The Deserter: "There used to be a system that connected the bunkers. Tunnels and such. Under the church and... everywhere. Most of them are gone now, collapsed -- just bricks. All the old infrastructure has..."

The Deserter: "Traitors. It's better alone." He nods toward Martinaise. "I watched the people of this city turn the lights back on, more and more each year. Ruins, glimmering in the dark, like a fucking merry-go-round..."
The Deserter: "Loyalist clown uniform..." He clears his throat, pointing at your coat. "I see they sent the full *fasces*. Royal treatment."
Empathy: Pride of the "at least we have this" kind. This is a cracked honour, a bitter pride. The man sounds like a *communard*. Be careful.
You: "One more time: what have you used this gun for?"
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""What have I used it for..." He loo..."]
You: "When did you first see the deceased?"
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""Three weeks ago, when the rich hag..."]
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""What?!" The old man's eyes fill wi..."]
JUMP OUT to SEAFORT / DESERTER ARREST
JUMP OUT to SEAFORT / DESERTER ARREST
The Deserter: "A big wheel of the 4th Regiment of the pederast army." He sighs. "To hell with it. It's a walking stick anyway...."
You: "You don't even have a magazine."
The Deserter: "You're right. It's a good thing I got one in the chamber."
Drama: Look at him raise his bushy brows. That's a lie. He's empty.
The Deserter: "Fucking clowns..." He squeezes his eyelids shut and shakes his head slowly.
The Deserter: "Fucking clown..." He squeezes his eyelids shut and shakes his head slowly.
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""No." The lieutenant aims his pisto..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: "No." The lieutenant aims his pistol square at the man's head and says:
You: "It's not wiped from the board. *I* remember it."
The Deserter: "They wouldn't like hearing their name in your mouth. A damn dog..."
You: "How does it go -- the song?"
You: "First, it wasn't *some Samaran shit*. It was 'Boy with a Scythe'..."
You: "La Revacholire... I've heard that name, somewhere else. In a dream."
You: "Thank you for clearing that up." (Conclude.)
You: "When I said I've talked to *her* -- you were curious."
The Deserter: "I've seen kids lose their minds and start *talking* to the city. Asking it to *protect* them, when the shelling gets bad. Calling it La Revacholire..."
Authority: Forget about that for a moment. You need to address that remark first.
Authority: You need to address that remark.
The Deserter: "Forty-three years... No." He looks into the fire -- a wisp of smoke rises from somewhere between the charred logs. "I've been on other islands too."

The Deserter: "I was on Rsurrection until they turned it into a *spa* in '18. Then I was on E48, a nameless sound, until the sea washed over it. Then I came back here. That was..." He thinks. "Twenty-two years ago."
The Deserter: "The boat engine." He gestures north. "On the water..."

Shivers: Where it's morning. On Rue de Saint-Ghislaine, people are walking, the gas streetlights have already been switched off. Further inland, in Jamrock, the streets come alive with workers: men, women, children rushing -- muddy avenue after muddy avenue. The temperature is rising. Altocumulus clouds form above Precinct 41.
The Deserter: "Always waiting." The old man turns his eyes from the shore and back to you.
You: "Once a deserter, always a deserter."
The Deserter: "I have done everything a man can do. What have *you* done?"
The Deserter: "A second is all it took."
The Deserter: He does not seemingly react to what you said. Only his right brow moves a little.
The Deserter: "That the bourgeois are not human."

The Deserter: "Aerostatics. The Landing had started. I climbed out -- into hell. There were ships all above. Hissing, whirling, and men pouring out. The chain was submerged so I had to swim back. The fortress was half submerged too, shattered."
Half Light: Some kind of great terror. Worse than you've ever seen.
The Deserter: "No you're not." He coughs. "You're a *liberast*."
The Deserter: "No..." He shakes his head. "The *opposite* of that. A future human, not a human of the past."
The Deserter: "No." He shakes his head: "Iblis -- Iblis calls it that."

The Deserter: "Rock and roll posturing..." He stares at the embers, then into your eyes. "You're the RCM -- you represent the Moralist International, the enemies of humanity, who took this city. I represent their adversary, le Parti communiste d'Insulinde."
You: "That's a *choice*. You could have become self-employed. Create the system."
The Deserter: "You're insane and grotesque. Everyone steals: vegetables, supplies. It's the life of a dog." He coughs once more, then puts his hand on his belly...
The Deserter: "Yes." There's a smile on his dry lips. "That is true, droite. That is true. That's the punishment in the jungle."
"Yes." There's a smile on his dry lips. "That is true, comrade. That is true. That is the punishment in the jungle."
You: "Thank you for clearing that up." (Conclude.)
The Deserter: "So you finally found it." He looks at you -- then pulls the raincoat tighter around his neck. "There must have been a small squadron's worth of arms in there. Belle-Magraves, right?"
Half Light: Grand, violent pride swells in him.
Drama: Not in a million years does he believe Cuno is armed. Perhaps it's the best end he can hope for?
The Deserter: "It's out of bullets." The old man lays the rifle down, carelessly, then looks at it lying there.
Cuno: "Hey..." The kid must have some idea. "You go to Martinaise lately? Cuno hasn't seen you around..."
JUMP OUT to SEAFORT / DESERTER BONUS
You: "Iosef Lilianovich Dros, you're under arrest for the murder of the colonel."
"Iosef Lilianovich Dros, you're under arrest for the murder of Ellis Kortenaer."
"Iosef Lilianovich Dros, you're under arrest for the murder of the Krenel colonel here in Martinaise."
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""Huh?" He leans closer with a stran..."]
The Deserter: ...then spits it out into the extinguished fire before him. He raises his black eyes, hooded by creased eyelids, to meet yours.
Perception (Sight): Unclouded by cataracts -- his eyesight is sharp.
Cuno: "Whoa... massive gun." Cuno looks at the weapon.
You: "How did you get hold of it?"
The Deserter: "The present to be afraid and cold." The old man pulls back the hood of his plastic cape and looks up into the sky. It's blue grey, the same colour as the sea.
The Deserter: "God's shithouse." He chortles. "Should've taken it down like they did in Graad; dismantled it for firewood."
Shivers: The cold dissipates. The old man watches you, carefully.
The Deserter: "Things keep falling apart if you don't tend to them."
Reaction Speed: Some kind of involuntary response? Something is slightly off with his motorics...
Visual Calculus: There, behind them, across the Delta -- the INSURCOM building. Coalition Government Insulindian Mission Control.
Empathy: It was dear to him. He resents forgetting it.
Encyclopedia: 'So if I can shoot rabbits then I can shoot fascists too' -- those are the next lines.
The Deserter: "Yes, I am from the Insulindian Citizens Militia. Recruited from Jamrock in '07, trained in the Ecole de Contrle Arien; consigned to emergency defence duties in '08."
You: "I come from there." (Point to the mainland.) "I can assure you, that is *not* what the people are planning."
The Deserter: "I am not a fool." He blinks his black eyes. "I know -- the material base for an uprising has eroded. The working class has betrayed mankind..."
The Deserter: "What *can* I do?" The old man suddenly looks around, suddenly confused.
The Deserter: "You're a lumpen with a gun." He looks away.
The Deserter: He looks away, to the sea, and lets out a cough.
You: "I'm not 'Coalition-appointed.' I just try to help people."
"We're not 'Coalition-appointed.' We just try to help people."
You: "We enforce the law. We keep these animals from killing each other."
You: "I know what it looks like. But I have secret plans to turn the RCM into a Mazovian revolutionary unit."
You: "I'm with the RCM -- let's leave it at that."
"We're with the RCM -- let's leave it at that."
The Deserter: "You're with the RCM --" He waves in your general direction. "The Coalition-appointed mob that oversees the occupation of Revachol. A so-called 'lieutenant'..."
Endurance: There's definitely something off with his body. Something more than just metabolism, or even cancer...
The Deserter: "No you're not. You're part of the *meat shield*." He squints. "The human shield that surrounds the fascists. While they kill and rape. That's what *you* are."
The Deserter: "There's nothing to look over. The triage is in and it's black. Administer morphine. Moribund."
Kim Kitsuragi: "In the city you move underground?"
The Deserter: The old man stares despondently at the logs. It's like he's forgotten you're there...
Cuno: "Oh yeah... that's hard core, Cuno's gonna like this."
The Deserter: "It's actually quite light. It was sent to us by our brothers in the Hsin-Yao Commune. Military aid." He pats the rifle.
The Deserter: "It was sent to us by our brothers in the Hsin-Yao Commune. Military aid." He pats the rifle.
You: "Okay, you can keep it -- but keep the gun down while we talk."
The Deserter: "You *fasces* are pathetic when you're alone..." He snorts. "To hell with it. It's a walking stick anyway..."
Conceptualization: You should engage him about inframaterialism. Impress him with all the *ideas* you picked up from the reading group.
Rhetoric: No, don't. This man does not subscribe to intellectual daydreams. The communism he mourns is a planetary force.
You: "That's it for now, old man. Stay put." [Leave.]
The Deserter: "Yeah-yeah, one move and you'll kill me. Put me against the wall..." He sighs. "To hell with it, it's a walking stick anyway."
The Deserter: "It's out of bullets." He lays the rifle down, slowly. Then just looks at it lying there.
Perception (Hearing): "I shoulda known they'd send the fucking clowns for me..." You hear him mumble to the blackened logs.
Authority: That was not the right move. You should have pushed on.
Conceptualization: He stares on, his wrinkled mouth moving without a sound -- a strange sadness, like a song.
You: Look at the butt of the gun.
You: "For Safre -- and for all mankind?"
Composure: He waves erratically -- with his hand, annoyed that he can't remember. A little tremor passes through him.
The Deserter: "I should've burned that console down..." He shakes his head.
You: "How did you know I was coming?"
You: "It was not rock-and-roll. It was Sad FM!"
The Deserter: "Sad FM, huh? I always hated that station. Phlegmatic, counter-revolutionary dirges... Sadness is a mental illness, a weapon of the bourgeoisie."
You: "I'm not a misanthrope, I'm a half-dead police officer who's just doing his job."
The Deserter: "The job of a shit-licker."
You: "She better come. I too have given my life to Mazovian socio-economics."
You: "Nothing in history is guaranteed. But revolution is still a possibility."
The Deserter: "No -- this is a vulgar criticism." He blinks his black eyes. "The material base for an uprising has eroded, the working class has betrayed mankind and themselves..."
The Deserter: "I just *mourn*." He stares right through you. Then blinks again.

The Deserter: "You could say I misunderstood the historic role of the proletariat, and thought Mazovian socio-economics were fallible. For a second I doubted the irreducible laws of historic materialism."
The Deserter: "Petty-bourgeois terror. It's in all men."
Perception (Hearing): Airships. Multi-rotored airships used in the Landing.

The Deserter: "I had to, I *had* to fight it. I had to never stop..." The old man falls silent. His black eyes keep piercing your skin as he looks to some great distance behind you, shaking his head slowly -- retreating from it.
Jump to: [Conceptualization: "These eyes are charred black by the..."]
Perception (Sight): A spray of blood from his mouth, on the black charcoal in the firepit...
The Deserter: "What?" The old man looks up -- the whites of his eyes are pale yellow.
The Deserter: "I don't think you did." He stares at the firepit. "You live in a delusion. Radio shows, speed racing, and sporting goods. It's not real..."
The Deserter: "You're inert lumpen with a gun."
You: (Nod appreciatively.) "I also live in Hell."

The Deserter: "At least you know it." He nods toward Martinaise. "The traitors of this city turned the lights back on in the Thirties, after the fighting stopped. Ruins, glittering in the dark, like a fucking merry-go-round..."
The Deserter: "They're good." He nods. "Plenty of tar. I like that boy on the pack too. Reminds me of the last century."
The Deserter: "Oh, I love it. Makes me nostalgic for the time we..." He pauses for a moment, catching his breath.
The Deserter: "The time we wiped every last fucking one of them off this Earth."
The Deserter: "What is it?" The old man looks around, confused. "What do you want from me? I can't go..."
You: No, he was just confused. Let it go...
Rhetoric: He would answer, but something happened. It's like his tape cut off suddenly...
JUMP OUT to SEAFORT / DESERTER BONUS
You: "I'm looking at another windbag who's got a problem with homo-sexuality."
The Deserter: "Did I offend your moralist sensibilities? You beat people to death with a baton, you fucking dog!" The old man spits.
You: "No, that's not it. I've talked to her."
The Deserter: "Talked to *her*?" He raises his bushy brow and looks down from the sky -- straight into your bloodshot eye.
Kim Kitsuragi: "The right type and the right calibre," the lieutenant nods -- glancing at the gun.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Jacketed -- military-grade ammunition. Stable in flight, good for hitting something that's very, very far away..." He says -- mostly to the old man.
You: "You're a holdover from, the ICM, the Insulindian Citizens Militia?"
The Deserter: "I did," he breathes out with a wheeze. "And you opened it -- how?"
The Deserter: "Real music. It's La Revacholire, you shit-licking boujee dog. *Chanson de soldat* of the black-and-whites."
You: "I don't even know what that is."
The Deserter: "It's inhuman. It's sick. It's not how a human being should live, but I had to..." He grimaces, clearly in pain. "I couldn't just forget. I couldn't just forget what I saw."
Jump to: [The Deserter: "The old man does not say more. Thos..."]
The Deserter: "It's not an island, droite." He looks around. "It's a defensive fortification of the Commune of Revachol and I am its last surviving defender."
The Deserter: "*The* Landing. Coalition military called it 'Operation Death Blow.'" He winces. "I later found out, on the radio -- they called it..."
Conceptualization: Sha'i'tan, Ahura, The Darkened One.
The Deserter: "Like you belong to the Moralist Party..." He squints his eyes at you.
The Deserter: The old man spits into the fire pit. He does not say anything more. A jitter passes his lower body...
Composure: The expression on his face is unreadable. There's some sort of interference there... neurological?
The Deserter: "How does anyone survive?" He looks at his worn running shoes. "I *steal*."
You: "The police can give you medical services. You need to be looked over."
"Yes. It may be serious. Cancer, even. The police can give you medical services. You need to be looked over."
"Yes. It may be serious. Cancer, even. The police can give you medical services. You need to be looked over."
"It may be serious. Cancer, even. The police can give you medical services. You need to be looked over."
The Deserter: "I *need* to die." A droll smile stretches across his mouth. "You don't have medical facilities, you have guns. That's all they give you, toy guns."
Drama: Even with the intensity he's putting in those words, and the fidgeting in his pocket, the kid is unconvincing.
The Deserter: "Disarmed by a kid..." He smiles to himself. "To hell with it. It's a walking stick anyway."
Jump to: [Cuno: ""No fucking way, not on Cuno's life..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: "What have you been doing during all this time?"
You: "What have you been doing all this time?"
You: (Now we are done.) "Iosef Lilianovich Dros, you are under arrest for the murder of the colonel."
(Now we are done.) "Iosef Lilianovich Dros, you are under arrest for the murder of Ellis Kortenaer."
(Now we are done.) "Iosef Lilianovich Dros, you are under arrest for the murder of the colonel known as Lely."
Encyclopedia: Southeast Samaran-made. Exotic. Must be defunct too. No modern rifle manufacturer of that name springs to mind.
Empathy: He's practically tearing up from spite. Hatred got the best of him a long time ago. This man hates everything.
The Deserter: "You don't fucking tell me what they sang..." He closes his eyes and exhales to calm himself.
